body:
What if Slim added a context object to the request under the `slim` attribute name:

```php
namespace Slim;

final class RequestAttributes
{
    public static function fromRequest(ServerRequestInterface $request): self;
    public function __construct(RouteInterface $route, RouteParserInterface $routeParser);
    public function getRoute(): RouteInterface;
    public function getRouteParser(): RouteParserInterface;
}
```

Accessible as:

```php
$slimAttributes = Slim\RequestAttributes::fromRequest($request);
// is the strongly typed version of:
$slimAttributes = $request->getAttribute('slim');
```

Hmm, after digging around in the code a bit, wouldn't it be easiest to add this to `App`?

```php
public function getRouteParser(): RouteParserInterface
{
    return new RouteParser($this->getRouteCollector());
}
```

Then someone can easily add `RouteParser` to their DIC:

```php
// Assuming Pimple or something like it
$container[RouteParserInterface::class] = function () use ($app) {
    return $app->getRouteParser();
};
```

Because really, that's what this is all about: being able to use the route parser for reverse routing.
